    "plan_content": "## Implementation Plan: Ollama Model Rename Feature\n\nAfter thoroughly studying the codebase, here's the complete plan across **4 files** and **7 discrete steps**:\n\n---\n\n### Files to modify\n\n| File | What changes |\n|---|---|\n| `api/types.go` | Add `RenameRequest` struct |\n| `api/client.go` | Add `Rename()` method on `*Client` |\n| `server/routes.go` | Add `RenameHandler()` + register `/api/rename` route |\n| `cmd/cmd.go` | Add `RenameHandler()` func + `renameCmd` + register it |\n\n---\n\n### Step 1 — `api/types.go`: `RenameRequest` struct\nPlaced after `CopyRequest` (~line 762), identical pattern:\n```go\ntype RenameRequest struct {\n    Source      string `json:\"source\"`\n    Destination string `json:\"destination\"`\n}\n```\n\n### Step 2 — `api/client.go`: `Rename()` method\nPlaced after `Copy()` (~line 387), same pattern:\n```go\nfunc (c *Client) Rename(ctx context.Context, req *RenameRequest) error {\n    return c.do(ctx, http.MethodPost, \"/api/rename\", req, nil)\n}\n```\n\n### Step 3 — `server/routes.go`: `RenameHandler()` method\nLogic flow:\n1. Bind JSON body, validate `Source`/`Destination` non-empty → 400\n2. `model.ParseName()` + `.IsValid()` on both → 400 + `errtypes.InvalidModelNameErrMsg`\n3. `manifest.ParseNamedManifest(dst)` — if err==nil (dest exists) → **409 Conflict**\n4. `CopyModel(src, dst)` — `os.ErrNotExist` → **404**, other error → 500\n5. Delete source: `manifest.ParseNamedManifest(src)` → `m.Remove()` → `m.RemoveLayers()` → 500 on failure\n6. Return **200** `{\"status\": \"success\"}`\n\nNo new imports needed — all packages (`manifest`, `model`, `errtypes`, `os`, `fmt`, `errors`, `io`, `gin`, `api`) are already imported in `routes.go`.\n\n### Step 4 — `server/routes.go`: Register route\nAfter the existing `/api/copy` line:\n```go\nr.POST(\"/api/copy\", s.CopyHandler)\nr.POST(\"/api/rename\", s.RenameHandler)\n```\n\n### Step 5 — `cmd/cmd.go`: `RenameHandler()` function\nAfter `CopyHandler` (~line 1350):\n```go\nfunc RenameHandler(cmd *cobra.Command, args []string) error {\n    client, _ := api.ClientFromEnvironment()\n    req := api.RenameRequest{Source: args[0], Destination: args[1]}\n    if err := client.Rename(cmd.Context(), &req); err != nil { return err }\n    fmt.Printf(\"Renamed \\\"%s\\\" to \\\"%s\\\"\\n\", args[0], args[1])\n    return nil\n}\n```\n\n### Steps 6 & 7 — `cmd/cmd.go`: `renameCmd` + registration\nDefine after `copyCmd`, with `Use: \"rename SOURCE DESTINATION\"`, `Args: cobra.ExactArgs(2)`, `PreRunE: checkServerHeartbeat`. Register in both the env-docs loop and `rootCmd.AddCommand(...)` after `copyCmd`.",
